---
import Copyable from '../components/Copyable.astro';
import ModeMixer from '../components/demo/ModeMixer.astro';
import RevealModes from '../components/demo/RevealModes.astro';
import SeasonPicker from '../components/demo/SeasonPicker.astro';
import ArborImage from '../components/graphics/ArborImage.astro';
import Divider from '../components/graphics/Divider.astro';
import Logo from '../components/graphics/Logo.astro';
import Button from '../components/system/Button.astro';
import Grid from '../components/system/Grid.astro';
import Layout from '../layouts/Homepage.astro';
---

<Layout>
	<div class="container">
		<nav class="@mode-dense">
			<div class="nav-start">
				<Logo class="nav-logo" />
				<h1 class="nav-title">Arbor CSS</h1>
				<SeasonPicker />
			</div>
			<ul class="nav-links">
				<li><a href="/docs">Documentation</a></li>
				<li><a href="https://github.com/a-type/arbor">GitHub</a></li>
			</ul>
		</nav>

		<div class="hero @mode-hero">
			<Grid class="hero-grid">
				<section style="grid-area: tagline;">
					<h1 class="tagline">
						The CSS<br /> Design System<br />
						<mark>System</mark>
						<div id="mark-bg"></div>
					</h1>
				</section>
				<section style="grid-area: logo;" class="logo-section">
					<ArborImage class="arbor-image" />
				</section>
				<section style="grid-area: description;">
					<p class="description">
						Scale your styling & enliven your designs,<br /> with <i>fewer</i> tokens
					</p>
				</section>
				<div class="cta @mode-normal">
					<Copyable class="button" value="npm install @arbor-css/core">
						<code>npm install @arbor-css/core</code>
					</Copyable>
					<Button tag="a" href="/docs">Read the docs</Button>
				</div>
			</Grid>
		</div>

		<Divider />

		<main>
			<section>
				<h2>Scale variations with modes</h2>
				<RevealModes>Show modes on this page</RevealModes>
				<p>
					Inspired by the <a href="https://mode.place">Mise en Mode</a> methodology,
					Arbor manages design variations with the powerful <em>mode</em> system,
					not token groups. Define one small set of tokens, then remix them with modes
					to quickly build out comprehensive treatments for things like <i
						>error</i
					>, <i>success</i>, <i>dense</i>, <i>hero</i>, and <i
						>anything you dream up</i
					>.
				</p>
				<ModeMixer />
			</section>
			<section>
				<h2>Design with rules, not artifacts</h2>
				<p>
					We call design tokens "decisions," but that's not really true -
					decisions are living rules; the tokens we export are just the outcome
					of those rules.
				</p>
				<p>
					Arbor gives you the full power of modern CSS to imbue your tokens with
					powerful, contextual, <i>real</i> rules. Adjust padding based on roundness.
					Calculate text metrics from a density global. Then watch as these rules
					produce emergent, consistent styles across the interface.
				</p>
			</section>
			<section>
				<h2>Your tokens, superpowered</h2>
				<p>
					Arbor comes with token validation, rich documentation, color previews,
					and editor suggestions for developers. Drive token adoption with
					carrot and stick.
				</p>
			</section>
			<section>
				<h2>Tomorrow's CSS, today</h2>
				<p>
					Arbor is forward-looking, using upcoming CSS standards like <code
						>@function</code
					> and <code>@mixin</code>, transformed with PostCSS to work in all
					browsers today. Arbor sprinkles in token dependency resolution,
					typechecking, and CSS simplification preprocessing on top.
				</p>
			</section>
			<section>
				<h2>Designers welcome</h2>
				<p>
					While Arbor takes a code-first approach to design systems to leverage
					code's power to define expressive logic, creating and iterating on
					modes is a matter of filling in values and watching the page come
					alive.
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>
	</div>

	<style>
		.container {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			max-width: min(800px, 90vw);
			margin: 0 auto;
			padding: var(--m-spacing-xl);
			gap: var(--m-spacing-xl);
		}

		.nav-logo {
			width: 32px;
			height: 32px;
		}

		.nav-title {
			@apply --mx-fg(inherit);
			font-size: var(--m-text-primary-size);
			font-weight: var(--m-primitive-typography-weight-bold);
			font-family: var(--m-text-primary-font);
			line-height: var(--m-text-primary-lineHeight);
			margin: 0;
		}

		.nav-start {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: row;
			align-items: center;
			gap: var(--m-spacing-lg);
			flex: 1;
		}

		.nav-links {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: row;
			gap: var(--m-spacing-lg);
			list-style: none;
			padding: 0;
			margin: 0;
		}

		nav {
			width: 100%;
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: row;
			gap: var(--m-spacing);
			padding: var(--m-spacing) 0;
			align-items: center;
			justify-content: between;
		}

		.hero {
			min-height: 50vh;
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: center;
			justify-content: center;
		}
		.hero-grid {
			grid-template-areas: 'logo' 'tagline' 'description' 'cta';
			grid-template-rows: minmax(200px, auto) auto auto;
			grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;

			border-radius: var(--m-surface-radius);

			@media (min-width: 400px) {
				grid-template-areas: 'tagline logo' 'description logo' 'cta logo';
				grid-template-rows: auto auto;
				grid-template-columns: 3fr 1fr;
			}
		}

		.tagline {
			position: relative;
			z-index: 1;
		}

		mark {
			anchor-name: --mark;
			@apply --mx-fg(var(--m-color-main-ink));
			@apply --mx-bg(transparent);
			padding: 0;
			border-radius: var(--m-action-radius);
			position: relative;
			z-index: 2;
		}

		#mark-bg {
			content: '';
			position: fixed;
			position-anchor: --mark;
			top: calc(anchor(top) + anchor-size(height) / 3);
			left: anchor(left);
			width: anchor-size(width);
			height: calc(anchor-size(height) / 2);
			@apply --mx-bg(var(--m-color-main-wash));
			border-radius: var(--m-action-radius);
			opacity: 0.5;
			z-index: 0;
		}

		main {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: var(--m-spacing-xl);
		}

		section {
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			align-items: start;
			justify-content: start;
			text-align: left;
			gap: var(--m-spacing);
		}

		.logo-section {
			gap: var(--m-spacing);
			box-sizing: border-box;
			display: flex;
			flex-direction: column;
			min-height: 0;
			align-items: center;
			justify-content: center;
		}

		.arbor-image {
			flex: 1;
		}

		.tagline {
			@apply --mx-fg(inherit);
			font-size: var(--m-text-primary-size);
			font-weight: var(--m-primitive-typography-weight-thin);
			font-family: var(--m-text-primary-font);
			line-height: var(--m-text-primary-lineHeight);
		}

		.description {
			@apply --mx-fg(inherit);
			font-size: var(--m-text-ambient-size);
			font-weight: var(--m-primitive-typography-weight-semiBold);
			font-family: var(--m-text-ambient-font);
			line-height: var(--m-text-ambient-lineHeight);
		}

		a {
			@apply --mx-fg(inherit);
			font-size: var(--m-text-secondary-size);
			font-weight: bold;
			font-family: var(--m-text-secondary-font);
			text-decoration: none;
			line-height: 1;
		}

		h1,
		h2,
		h3,
		p {
			margin: 0;
		}

		.cta {
			grid-area: cta;
			display: flex;
			gap: var(--m-spacing);
			flex-wrap: wrap;
		}
	</style>
</Layout>
